## 
# Invalid Credentials
# 
# Simulates valid API endpoint but incorrect credentials.
# 
# Expected Behavior:
#   - The script logs HTTP 401 or 403 errors when accessing the endpoint.
#   - Sends a “down” notification and retries as configured.
# 
# Test command:
# `../check_endpoint.sh > invalid_credentials.log 2>&1`
# 
# Verify:
#   - Verify logs contain HTTP 401 or 403 response codes:
#     `grep "API request failed" invalid_credentials.log`
# 
HASS_API_URL="http://valid-api-url/api"
HASS_AUTH_TOKEN="invalid_token"
SMS_TO="+1234567890"
SMS_FROM="sender@example.com"
ENDPOINT_DOWN_MESSAGE="API is down."
ENDPOINT_UP_MESSAGE="API is back online."